  "prompt": "What is the minimum level of mathematical proficiency required to graduate from West Point?",
  "response": "To graduate from the United States Military Academy at West Point, cadets are required to complete a rigorous academic curriculum that includes a strong emphasis on mathematics. The minimum level of mathematical proficiency typically involves the completion of courses in calculus and differential equations, as well as probability and statistics. Cadets must demonstrate competency in these areas to fulfill graduation requirements.\n\nAdditionally, incoming cadets typically are expected to have a solid foundation in high school mathematics, including algebra and geometry. However, the exact proficiency requirements may evolve, so it's advisable for prospective students to check the latest academic requirements from West Point's official resources or admissions office.",
